text: The 2018 Minnesota gubernatorial election took place on November 6, to elect the 41st Governor of Minnesota. Democratic (DFL) Governor Mark Dayton chose not to run for re-election for a third term. The Democratic nominee was U.S. Representative Tim Walz from Minnesota's 1st congressional district while the Republican Party nominated Hennepin County commissioner Jeff Johnson. Walz went on to defeat Johnson by the largest margin for a DFL candidate since 1986, receiving more votes than any other gubernatorial candidate in Minnesota history. ==Results== ==References== Category:21st century in Minnesota Category:2018 in the United States Category:Gubernatorial elections in the United States Category:November 2018 events
